There is a chance that everyone's face,
except mine, has been seen by Kira.

125
00:10:29,130 --> 00:10:31,841
Kira might have written down
their names already.

126
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:36,178
So, for an hour...no, half an hour,

127
00:10:36,262 --> 00:10:40,349
I want to see if anyone
falls under Kira's control or dies.

128
00:10:40,808 --> 00:10:44,353
W-What?
He's waiting to see if we die?

129
00:10:44,562 --> 00:10:47,898
<i>He's right...
It's not impossible if Light is Kira.</i>

130
00:10:48,274 --> 00:10:51,068
<i>Especially now,
since we 're expendable...</i>

131
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:33,444
<i>This is just a front...
to buy some time. . .Near...</i>

132
00:11:34,111 --> 00:11:37,990
<i>I never thought it would be so hard
to keep myself from laughing.</i>

133
00:11:38,908 --> 00:11:41,118
<i>Near's probably waiting
for him t0 come.</i>

134
00:11:41,452 --> 00:11:42,536
<i>I've already predicted that.</i>

135
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:51,795
Near! It's been over thirty minutes.
Nothing's happened.

136
00:11:52,129 --> 00:11:55,132
Of course.
It's because Kira isn't here.

137
00:11:56,717 --> 00:11:59,261
Fine. Everyone seems safe.

138
00:12:00,095 --> 00:12:01,430
I'll remove my mask.

139
00:12:23,369 --> 00:12:25,037
What's wrong, Near?

140
00:12:26,163 --> 00:12:27,998
Are you still waiting for something?

141
00:12:29,792 --> 00:12:32,336
Waiting... That's right.

142
00:12:33,170 --> 00:12:38,634
I am waiting. . .for the one who
will solve everything, to arrive.

143
00:12:39,009 --> 00:12:40,928
"The one who will
solve everything?"

144
00:12:41,095 --> 00:12:44,640
He'll come soon.
So we must wait.

145
00:12:44,932 --> 00:12:46,684
This building is completely sealed.

146
00:12:47,309 --> 00:12:50,145
You can't see inside without
opening that door.

147
00:12:51,230 --> 00:12:55,567
He'll come through that door...
or at least peek through it...

148
00:12:56,694 --> 00:12:58,028
Who's going to come?

149
00:12:59,029 --> 00:13:02,992
X-Kira. He's the one who is
currently killing in Kira's place...

150
00:13:03,575 --> 00:13:09,373
He'll come with the notebook.
And he'll see me and write my name.

151
00:13:09,665 --> 00:13:13,002
No, he'll probably try
to kill everyone here

152
00:13:13,085 --> 00:13:14,920
who knows about
the notebook's existence.

153
00:13:18,507 --> 00:13:21,260
Th-This makes no sense.
What are you talking about?!

154
00:13:21,343 --> 00:13:23,095
Are you saying that
some third party...

155
00:13:23,178 --> 00:13:26,640
is just going to come strolling by
with the notebook and kill us?!

156
00:13:26,724 --> 00:13:28,851
And are you saying that we should
just let this happen?!

157
00:13:29,601 --> 00:13:31,770
That's right...
Please listen.

158
00:13:32,479 --> 00:13:36,984
If someone comes through that door,
just let him in...

159
00:13:37,151 --> 00:13:41,030
If the door opens slightly,
act as if you don't notice.

160
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:43,615
Th-That's crazy. That's. . .!

161
00:13:45,701 --> 00:13:46,785
He's already here.

162
00:14:03,761 --> 00:14:05,429
LIGHT YAGAMI

163
00:14:05,429 --> 00:14:06,430
God!

164
00:14:17,149 --> 00:14:18,609
Delete.

165
00:14:19,109 --> 00:14:22,071
Delete. Delete. Delete. Delete.

166
00:14:23,489 --> 00:14:27,117
Delete. Delete. Delete. Delete.
Delete!

167
00:14:27,451 --> 00:14:29,787
Delete. Delete. Delete.

168
00:14:30,954 --> 00:14:32,122
Delete.

169
00:14:32,373 --> 00:14:33,540
Please do not move.

170
00:14:33,624 --> 00:14:35,417
It's all right. You won't die.

171
00:14:35,501 --> 00:14:38,712
- How can you be so sure, Near?!
- Delete. Delete. Delete. Delete.

172
00:14:38,796 --> 00:14:40,464
I've tampered with the notebook.

173
00:14:41,215 --> 00:14:44,343
We took possession of the notebook
and replaced its pages.

174
00:14:44,426 --> 00:14:47,930
The person behind the door...
who is killing for Kira...

175
00:14:48,097 --> 00:14:50,641
has been using exactly
one page every day.

176
00:14:50,724 --> 00:14:55,479
So I replaced the pages for today and
all subsequent days so no one will die.

177
00:14:55,813 --> 00:14:58,399
Delete. Delete. Delete.
Delete. Delete...

178
00:14:58,482 --> 00:15:00,401
Delete. Delete. Delete.
Delete. Delete!

179
00:15:00,776 --> 00:15:01,819
Delete!

180
00:15:02,069 --> 00:15:06,490
Delete!

181
00:15:27,344 --> 00:15:29,346
X-Kira, who's beyond that door...

182
00:15:29,430 --> 00:15:31,974
will eventually look inside...

183
00:15:32,558 --> 00:15:34,518
to see if we're dead.

184
00:15:35,185 --> 00:15:37,312
We can catch him when he does.

185
00:15:37,896 --> 00:15:41,525
The one whose name isn't written
in the notebook is Kira.

186
00:15:43,652 --> 00:15:47,865
Y-You're right. . .The one whose name
isn't written down would be Kira...

187
00:15:48,615 --> 00:15:49,700
But...

188
00:16:03,464 --> 00:16:04,631
<i>Exactly as planned!
Exactly as planned!</i>

189
00:16:04,715 --> 00:16:06,133
<i>Exactly as planned!</i>

190
00:16:12,264 --> 00:16:15,434
<i>Tampering with the notebook...
I knew it all along.</i>

191
00:16:15,726 --> 00:16:18,729
<i>Near... You've been completely defeated!</i>

192
00:16:19,771 --> 00:16:23,400
<i>The notebook you tampered with
was the fake that I had Mikami prepare!</i>

193
00:16:24,109 --> 00:16:27,112
<i>And now, the one Mikami is
writing names in...</i>

194
00:16:27,196 --> 00:16:29,698
<i>is the real notebook
that's been hidden!</i>

195
00:16:39,708 --> 00:16:42,252
<i>I had Mikami make a fake notebook</i>

196
00:16:42,544 --> 00:16:45,923
<i>and send Takada clippings
from the real one.</i>

197
00:16:46,924 --> 00:16:50,802
<i>In other words, Takada was the one
who was really doing the killings...</i>

198
00:16:51,178 --> 00:16:56,225
<i>I had Mikami write names in public,
numerous times in the fake notebook...</i>

199
00:16:56,308 --> 00:16:58,852
<i>so he would be noticed if
he was being followed.</i>

200
00:16:59,436 --> 00:17:03,273
<i>But even then, Takada was the one
who was doing the killings...</i>

201
00:17:03,815 --> 00:17:05,734
<i>That is how I made them believe</i>

202
00:17:05,901 --> 00:17:08,737
<i>that the Notebook that Mikami
had was the real one...</i>

203
00:17:10,405 --> 00:17:14,535
<i>Mikami's daily behavior can
be called morbidly methodical.</i>

204
00:17:14,868 --> 00:17:18,789
<i>He fills the notebook
with names one page a day...</i>

205
00:17:19,831 --> 00:17:24,586
<i>Near. You noticed that and thought
of tampering with it.</i>

206
00:17:25,712 --> 00:17:28,590
<i>In other words, you arranged it so that
on the day of our meeting,</i>

207
00:17:28,674 --> 00:17:29,883
<i>the page would be on the right side.</i>

208
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:33,470
<i>You just had to change
the pages for that day on.</i>

209
00:17:34,846 --> 00:17:35,889
<i>If you did,</i>

210
00:17:35,973 --> 00:17:38,433
<i>no one would die from having
their names written in the notebook...</i>

211
00:17:38,976 --> 00:17:40,477
<i>That was your plan!</i>

212
00:17:41,103 --> 00:17:43,188
<i>That's why the meeting date
was not changed.</i>

213
00:17:44,523 --> 00:17:48,652
<i>But I knew you were going to
tamper with the notebook, so...</i>

214
00:17:48,944 --> 00:17:50,237
<i>I had Mikami</i>

215
00:17:50,237 --> 00:17:51,446
MATS U M OTO

216
00:17:51,446 --> 00:17:52,531
<i>check the notebook every day...</i>

217
00:17:54,074 --> 00:17:55,284
I've confirmed it.

218
00:18:01,832 --> 00:18:04,543
<i>This match was decided
at that point...</i>

219
00:18:05,168 --> 00:18:10,591
<i>The notebook that Mikami brought today
is the real one I had him hide!</i>

220
00:18:15,971 --> 00:18:21,852
<i>Bu! Near, you had a chance.
You 're sofi'...</i>

221
00:18:23,061 --> 00:18:25,022
<i>You're nowhere as good as L...</i>

222
00:18:26,356 --> 00:18:27,816
<i>I would have noticed</i>

223
00:18:27,899 --> 00:18:31,528
<i>there was a possibility that the notebook
was fake and would have tested it.</i>

224
00:18:32,070 --> 00:18:33,864
